author: fmeschbe
msg: FELIX-1962 Provide a ProxyListener analogous to the ProxyServlet to be called by the actual listener registered with the servlet container and to forward the events to the registered listeners.

author: fmeschbe
msg: FELIX-1962 Register the EventDispatcher for it to be available in the ProxyListener (see the HTTP proxy bundle)

author: fmeschbe
msg: FELIX-1962 Support for listeners in the base bundle: Context Attribute and Request Attribute as well as request events are handled from within. Session and Session Attribute events are handled through a hook request to be installed in the actual servlet container. This works with the EventDispatcher class similarly to the DispatcherServlet.
